reviewText: Great

Love Finds You in Valentine is worth MORE than the original high price.  Many interesting subplots. The developing relationship between Kennedy & Derek is central. The actors were unknown to me, but their chemistry develops from intriguing, rocky beginning through some bumps to a satisfying conclusion. Some great dialog. Beautiful scenery. There is some faith & love of neighbor true of Christians around the world. I waited months to see it. Worth the wait. Watched 6 times so far.

Irene Brand writes a great story in Love Finds You in Valentine, with lots of twists and turns and a little more to the plot than the movie could show.  It is a fast-paced page turner.  The DVD was also good, but not as full a story as the book.
Very nice family movie for all audiences.

I enjoyed love finds you in charm, and the makers of that movie made this movie so I took a chance on it without watching it on TV first. It was actually pretty good. There is a little adventure and a little mystery involved, and of course romance. I recommend this movie.

Got this movie because found out it was filmed near me (Millersburg, OH).  Great photography of this beautiful area is backdrop for a family-friendly romantic story.  After being impressed by the leading man, I "Googled" him.  He portrayed Jesus in TV mini-series, "The Bible."  So, I then bought that.  WOW.  What an acting range this man has!  Highly recommend all of the "Love Finds You In...." movies.  Check it out.  There are two others!

Love Finds you in Valentine. A romance movie with a bit of intrigue, family feud, and beautiful scenery. The movie is set in Nebraska, but was filmed in Millersburg Ohio. Ed Asner and Lindsey Wagner held supporting roles. Although a romance, it was not cheesy or syrupy.
The movie did not drag, but had a decent pace. The acting was good as well.
